  <slide> 
    <title>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.0</title>
    <contents>

      <p>
        <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG" target="_specification">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.0</a>
      </p>

      <details>
        <summary>Disability Access Requirements</summary>
        <ul>
          <li>Technology agnostic</li>
          <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG20/quickref/">How to Meet WCAG 2.0</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/UNDERSTANDING-WCAG20/">Understanding WCAG 2.0</a></li>
          <li>Understanding requires knowledge of features of specific technogies</li>
          <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20-TECHS/">Techniques for WCAG 2.0</a></li>
          <li>Techniques are <strong>not</strong> normative or comprehensive</li>
        </ul>
      </details>

      <img src="images/wcag20-title.png" width="99%" alt="Graphical browser rendering of title portion of WCAG 2.0 Guidelines"/>
    </contents>
  </slide> 

  <slide> 
    <title>Accessible Rich Internet Applications (ARIA) 1.0</title>
    <contents>

      <p>
        <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria" target="_specification">Accessible Rich Internet Applications 1.0</a>
      </p>
      
      <details>
        <summary>Standardized Support Accessibility APIs</summary>
        <ul>
          <li><code>role</code> semantics</li>
          <li>Accessible name</li>
          <li>Accessible description</li>
          <li>States and properties</li>
          <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-practices/">WAI-ARIA 1.0 Authoring Practices</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI/PF/aria-implementation/">WAI-ARIA 1.0 User Agent Implementation Guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/core-aam-1.1/">Core Accessibility API Mappings 1.1</a></li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      
      <img src="images/wai-aria-title.png" width="99%" alt="Graphical browser rendering of title portion of W3C ARIA 1.0 Specfication"/>
    </contents>
  </slide> 

  <slide> 
    <title>HTML 5.x</title>
    <contents>
      <p>
        <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/html5" target="_specification">HTML 5 Specification</a>
      </p>
      
      <details>
        <summary>Standardized Support Accessibility APIs</summary>
        <ul>
          <li>Default <code>role</code> semantics</li>
          <li><code>role</code> semantics restrictions</li>
          <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/aria-in-html/">W3C Notes on Using ARIA in HTML</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://specs.webplatform.org/html-aria/webspecs/master/">ARIA in HTML</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/html-aapi/">W3C HTML to Platform Accessibility APIs Implementation Guide</a></li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      

      <img src="images/html5-title.png" width="99%" alt="Title portion of W3C HTML 5 Specification"/>
    </contents>
  </slide> 

  <slide> 
    <title>HTML 5: main element</title>
    <contents>
      <p>
        <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/html5/grouping-content.html#the-main-element" target="_specification">HTML 5: main element</a>
      </p>

      <details>
        <summary>Meets an important accessibility requirement</summary>
        <ul>
          <li>Default <code>role</code> semantics</li>
          <li><code>role</code> semantics restrictions</li>
          <li>Standardize accessibility API mappings</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      
      <img src="images/html5-main.png" width="99%" alt="Graphical browser rendering of main element section of W3C HTML 5 Specification"/>
    </contents>
  </slide> 

